30/04/2006
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- NATO foreign ministers agreed on Friday (28 April) that KFOR will preserve its current level of 17,000 troops until the status of the province is settled. NATO spokesman James Appathurai said the decision was reached at a two-day informal meeting of top diplomats of the Alliance's member countries held in the Bulgarian capital. They also reaffirmed their strong support for efforts by UN special envoy Martti Ahtisaari. The fourth round of negotiations on Kosovo begins Thursday in Vienna. (UPI, Reuters, RTS, AP - 28/04/06)
